I took that out in a later version of this doc though. I'm not sure why you're seeing it?

I realize you **can** use a positional as a keyword and pass a keyword as positional, but that opens the door for more states than one could possibly hope to wrangle.

The most relevant surface is what we **provide**, i.e. what is defined in our code and indicated in our docs. I have seen people who consider all arguments to be allowed as positional and this makes updating APIs very difficult.

@jonparrott and I have discussed before and determined that the order of keywords should not be a deciding factor in API changes.

It's annoying that GH is not allowing comments on folded lines... :unamused: 

